  "text": "Tagore gave importance on spiritual and moral education rather than on scriptural knowledge for an integral development of a human. He considered cooperation, selfless activities, love towards fellows and a responsibility towards nurturing social relationships to be the main purpose of one\"s informed mind. It, he argued, enabled the individual to live as a worthy being [CITATION_1] .",
